In article <strnlghtCqA5nM.JxG@netcom.com>,
David Sternlight <david@sternlight.com> wrote:
 
> As I understand it a license is simply a special form of
>contract. if so, no meeting of the minds, no license, thus any use of RSAREF
>by the person claiming to be licensed but who has "interpreted" an ambiguous
>term differently from RSADSI, particularly after being told he is so doing,
>is infringing.

Were this reasoning valid, any contract over which there was a dispute
in its terms would be held invalid.  This does not generally occur, so
we must conclude the reasoning invalid, or at best, incompletely qualified.

